@antinucleon I've create an update Makefile that fixes the problem with an extended `ARCH` argument. Example:
`make ANDROID=1 ARCH=arm64`

I'm happy to update the `Readme.md` and create a pull request?

@piiswrong: you mention that:

> Also returned NDArrayHandle can be different from the ones passed in. So always create new NDArray objects from returned handle.

However, in the Python wrapper, the passed in output NDArrays are simply [being returned](https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet/blob/3a820bf7526d5c78f418a0ec2b01d4cd9977bbe7/python/mxnet/_ctypes/ndarray.py#L132) after calling `MXImperativeInvoke`. Am I misunderstanding something? 

@taliesinb
